Module kivakit.primitive.collections
Package com.telenav.kivakit.primitive.collections.list

Interface LongList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.numeric.Countable, LongCollection, LongIterable, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, PrimitiveList, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.interfaces.numeric.Sized
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LongArray, PackedArray, SplitLongArray, SplitPackedArray
    public interface LongList
extends LongCollection, PrimitiveList
    A long collection supporting indexed operations. The first and last values in the list can be retrieved with first() and last(). Values at a given index can be altered and retrieved with clear(int), get(int), safeGet(int) and set(int, long).

    If the list is sorted, it can be searched with binarySearch(long), which returns the index of the value if it is found and a value less than zero if it is not.

    A default iterator implementation is provided by iterator().

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
